node.title: Victoria records 1,193 new COVID-19 cases and 13 deaths
node.alt: The Melbourne city skyline, looking over trams and the Princes Bridge.
node.description: There are now 11,457 active cases of the virus in Victoria, and 595 people have died during the current outbreak.
node.content:
["Victoria has recorded 1,193\u00a0new local COVID-19 cases and 13\u00a0deaths, as authorities confirm another two new cases of the\u00a0Omicron variant in Melbourne\u00a0from returned international travellers.", "There are now 11,457\u00a0active cases of the virus in Victoria, and 595\u00a0people have died during the current outbreak.", "There are 323\u00a0people in hospital, of whom 68\u00a0are in intensive care and 29\u00a0are on a ventilator.", "A further 44\u00a0people are in ICU but their infections are no longer considered active.", "The new cases were detected from 82,895\u00a0test results received yesterday.", "The health department confirmed there were three cases of the Omicron variant in Victoria.", "Two people who travelled from Dubai to Melbourne on November 30 are confirmed to have the Omicron strain, while genomic sequencing is under way to confirm if a third COVID-positive person on the flight is carrying the Omicron variant.", "The state\u2019s first case was confirmed on Wednesday, and was a returned traveller in hotel quarantine.", "", "
Why we hear about some COVID-19 variants more than others
"]
